p%3EIn%20a%20healthy%2C%20thriving%20workplace%2C%20colleagues%20aren't%20throwing%20each%20other%20under%20the%20bus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20don't%20show%20up%20to%20work%20at%20their%20best%20when%20they%20don't%20feel%20safe%2C%20says%20Leena%20Rinne%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20leadership%2C%20business%2C%20and%20coaching%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-viral-trust-in-employees-why-thats-a-good-thing-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESkillsoft%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20an%20educational%20technology%20company%20that%20produces%20learning%20management%20system%20software%20and%20content.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20version%20of%20myself%20I%20bring%20every%20day%20is%20very%20different%20if%20I'm%20constantly%20nervous%2C%20if%20I%20don't%20have%20the%20psychological%20safety%2C%20and%20if%20I'm%20not%20clear%20on%20how%20I%20contribute%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20way%20to%20build%20that%20trust%20is%20to%20encourage%20making%20mistakes%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20the%20responsibility%20of%20bosses%2C%20Rinne%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLeaders%20sometimes%20feel%20like%20they%20have%20to%20have%20the%20answers%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20why%20they%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20asking%20for%20input%20or%20admitting%20when%20they've%20done%20something%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20I'm%20not%20afraid%20to%20make%20mistakes%2C%20I'm%20willing%20to%20take%20more%20risks%2C%20which%20means%20I'm%20willing%20to%20innovate%20more%20effectively.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Leena%20Rinne%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680a0aebc6ad288d147f0142%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22854%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELeena%20Rinne%20is%20a%20vice%20president%20at%20Skillsoft.%3Cp%3ESkillsoft%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELeaders%20who%20are%20ab