could%20decline%20another%2010%25%20before%20bottoming%20out%20in%202027%2C%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman%20Sachs'%20report%20was%20based%20on%20an%20analysis%20of%20housing%20bust%20episodes%20across%2015%20economies%20since%201960%2C%20which%20found%20that%20the%20median%20housing%20price%20correction%20is%2030%25%20over%20six%20years.%20Goldman%20Sachs%20defines%20housing%20busts%20as%20a%20decline%20of%2020%25%20from%20cyclical%20peaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20the%20durability%20of%20housing%20stock%20and%20stickiness%20of%20house%20prices%2C%20it%20may%20take%20years%20for%20housing%20busts%20to%20finally%20find%20a%20bottom%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20analysts%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20property%20market%20showed%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-recovery-property-crisis-consumption-trump-trade-war-tariffs-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egreen%20shoots%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20with%20slowing%20price%20declines%2C%20but%20recent%20months%20saw%20renewed%20weakness%20in%20both%20prices%20and%20activity.%20In%20May%2C%20new-home%20prices%20in%2070%20cities%20posted%20their%20biggest%20decline%20in%20seven%20months%2C%20while%20used-home%20prices%20witnessed%20their%20sharpest%20fall%20in%20eight%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20unfolding%20housing%20market%20correction%20in%20China%20represents%20one%20of%20the%20decade's%20most%20significant%20economic%20events%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20the%20analysts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crisis%20began%20in%202021%2C%20when%20Beijing%20implemented%20higher%20lending%20curbs%20for%20both%20developers%20and%20buyers%20to%20rein%20in%20excessive%20borrowing%20by%20property%20developers%20and%20reduce%20systemic%20financial%20risk%20in%20the%20real%20estate%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20curbs%20triggered%20a%20sharp%20slowdown%20in%20China's%20decades-long%20housing%20boom%20%E2%80%94%20once%20a%20key%20economic%20engine%20%E2%80%94%20and%20compounded%20the%20pain%20from%20strict%20pandemic%20restrictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20the%20world's%20second%20largest%20%E2%80%94%20is%20not%20just%20dealing%20with%20its%20long-drawn%20property%20crisis.%20It's%20also%20facing%20high%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-rat-people-broke-burnt-out-social-media-unemployment-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyouth%20unemployment%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-deflation-stimulus-government-property-bubble-unemployment-growth-prices-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edeflationary%20pressures%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-cpi-deflation-inflation-home-appliance-trade-in-subsidies-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eweak%20consumer%20sentiment.%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20mounting%20pressure%2C%20Chinese%20policymakers%20have%20remained%20cautious%20in%20rolling%20out%20monetary%20and%20fiscal%20support%2C%20which%20is%20%26quot%3Bin%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20other%20countries'%20reactions%20to%20significant%20housing%20downturns%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20the%20analysts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInsufficient%20cyclical%20easing%20is%20likely%20to%20result%20in%20sustained%20weakness%20in%20confidence%20and%20private%20demand%20as%20well%20as%20prolonged%20deflation%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysts%20expect%20the%20Chinese%20government%20to%20move%20to%20ease%20policy%20should%20property%20prices%20fall%20sharply%2C%20exports%20slow%2C%20or%20unemployment%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina's%20limited%20policy%20response%20relative%20to%20historical%20norms%20suggests%20more%20policy%20easing%20remains%20necessary%20to%20prevent%20the%20housing%20downturn%20from%20causing%20entrenched%20demand%20weakness%2C%20though%20political%20willingness%20rather%20than%20capacity%20usually%20p